    {
      id: "india-kekaisaran-mughal-akbar",
      langs: {
        id: {
          title: "Kekaisaran Mughal dan Akbar yang Agung: Sinkretisme Budaya di Puncak Kejayaan",
          desc: "Kaisar Akbar memerintah Kekaisaran Mughal dengan kebijakan toleransi beragama yang revolusioner, menyatukan sebagian besar anak benua India sekaligus menciptakan sinkretisme budaya Hindu-Islam yang unik.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Kekaisaran Mughal didirikan pada 1526 oleh Babur, seorang penguasa keturunan Timur Lenk dan Genghis Khan dari Asia Tengah, yang berhasil mengalahkan Kesultanan Delhi dalam Pertempuran Panipat Pertama, meletakkan fondasi bagi salah satu kekaisaran paling berpengaruh dalam sejarah India.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Kekaisaran ini mencapai puncak kejayaannya di bawah pemerintahan cucu Babur, Akbar, yang naik takhta pada 1556 di usia hanya 13 tahun namun berkembang menjadi salah satu penguasa paling visioner dalam sejarah India, memperluas wilayah kekaisaran melalui kombinasi penaklukan militer dan aliansi diplomatik dengan para penguasa Rajput Hindu.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Akbar dikenal khususnya karena kebijakan toleransi beragama yang jauh mendahului zamannya, menghapuskan pajak jizyah yang membebani warga non-Muslim, menikahi putri-putri Rajput Hindu, serta menciptakan Din-i-Ilahi, sebuah sinkretisme filosofis yang menggabungkan elemen-elemen dari Islam, Hinduisme, Kristen, dan agama-agama lain di istananya.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Era Mughal di bawah Akbar dan penerus-penerusnya menyaksikan perkembangan seni dan arsitektur yang luar biasa, menggabungkan elemen Persia, India, dan Islam Asia Tengah menjadi gaya arsitektur Indo-Islam yang khas, sebuah tradisi yang kelak melahirkan mahakarya seperti Taj Mahal yang dibangun cucu Akbar, Shah Jahan.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Sistem administrasi Mughal yang efisien, termasuk reformasi sistem perpajakan dan tata kelola provinsi yang diperkenalkan Akbar, menciptakan fondasi birokrasi yang bertahan hingga periode kolonial Inggris berikutnya, sementara warisan sinkretisme budaya Mughal terus membentuk identitas budaya India hingga saat ini meski kekaisaran tersebut akhirnya melemah dan runtuh pada abad ke-18 dan ke-19.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Akbar",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — Akbar",
          source2: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.worldhistory.org/Akbar/",
          sourceSnippet2: "World History Encyclopedia — Akbar",
          source3: "UNESCO World Heritage",
          sourceUrl3: "https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/251/",
          sourceSnippet3: "UNESCO World Heritage — Fatehpur Sikri, Akbar's capital"
        },
        en: {
          title: "The Mughal Empire and Akbar the Great: Cultural Syncretism at Its Peak",
          desc: "Emperor Akbar ruled the Mughal Empire with revolutionary religious tolerance policies, unifying most of the Indian subcontinent while creating a unique Hindu-Islamic cultural syncretism.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">The Mughal Empire was founded in 1526 by Babur, a ruler descended from Timur and Genghis Khan from Central Asia, who successfully defeated the Delhi Sultanate in the First Battle of Panipat, laying the foundation for one of the most influential empires in Indian history.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">This empire reached its peak under the rule of Babur's grandson, Akbar, who ascended the throne in 1556 at only 13 years old but developed into one of the most visionary rulers in Indian history, expanding the empire's territory through a combination of military conquest and diplomatic alliances with Hindu Rajput rulers.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Akbar was particularly known for religious tolerance policies far ahead of his time, abolishing the jizya tax that burdened non-Muslim citizens, marrying Hindu Rajput princesses, and creating Din-i-Ilahi, a philosophical syncretism combining elements from Islam, Hinduism, Christianity, and other religions at his court.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The Mughal era under Akbar and his successors witnessed extraordinary artistic and architectural development, combining Persian, Indian, and Central Asian Islamic elements into a distinctive Indo-Islamic architectural style, a tradition that would later produce masterpieces such as the Taj Mahal built by Akbar's grandson, Shah Jahan.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The efficient Mughal administrative system, including tax reforms and provincial governance introduced by Akbar, created a bureaucratic foundation that endured into the subsequent British colonial period, while the legacy of Mughal cultural syncretism continues to shape Indian cultural identity to this day, though the empire eventually weakened and collapsed in the 18th and 19th centuries.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Akbar",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — Akbar",
          source2: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.worldhistory.org/Akbar/",
          sourceSnippet2: "World History Encyclopedia — Akbar",
          source3: "UNESCO World Heritage",
          sourceUrl3: "https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/251/",
          sourceSnippet3: "UNESCO World Heritage — Fatehpur Sikri, Akbar's capital"
        },
        ja: {
          title: "ムガル帝国とアクバル大帝：文化的融合の頂点",
          desc: "アクバル帝は革新的な宗教的寛容政策でムガル帝国を統治し、インド亜大陸の大部分を統一すると同時に独自のヒンドゥー・イスラム文化融合を生み出した。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">ムガル帝国は1526年、中央アジア出身でティムールとチンギス・ハーンの子孫である統治者バーブルによって建国され、第一次パーニーパットの戦いでデリー・スルタン朝を打ち破ることに成功し、インド史上最も影響力のある帝国の一つの基盤を築きました。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">この帝国はバーブルの孫アクバルの統治下で最盛期を迎えました。彼はわずか13歳で1556年に即位しましたが、インド史上最も先見性のある統治者の一人へと成長し、軍事征服とヒンドゥー教ラージプート統治者との外交同盟の組み合わせを通じて帝国領土を拡大しました。</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Akbar",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — アクバル",
          source2: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.worldhistory.org/Akbar/",
          sourceSnippet2: "World History Encyclopedia — アクバル"
        },
        ko: {
          title: "무굴 제국과 아크바르 대제: 문화적 융합의 정점",
          desc: "아크바르 황제는 혁신적인 종교적 관용 정책으로 무굴 제국을 통치하며 인도 아대륙 대부분을 통일하는 동시에 독특한 힌두-이슬람 문화 융합을 만들어냈다.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">무굴 제국은 1526년 중앙아시아 출신으로 티무르와 칭기즈칸의 후손인 통치자 바부르에 의해 건국되었으며, 그는 제1차 파니파트 전투에서 델리 술탄국을 성공적으로 물리치고 인도 역사상 가장 영향력 있는 제국 중 하나의 기초를 마련했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">이 제국은 바부르의 손자 아크바르의 통치 하에 전성기를 맞았으며, 그는 불과 13세의 나이로 1556년 즉위했지만 인도 역사상 가장 선견지명 있는 통치자 중 한 명으로 성장하여 군사 정복과 힌두 라지푸트 통치자들과의 외교 동맹을 결합해 제국 영토를 확장했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">아크바르는 특히 시대를 훨씬 앞선 종교적 관용 정책으로 유명했으며, 비무슬림 시민에게 부담을 주던 지즈야 세금을 폐지하고, 힌두 라지푸트 공주들과 결혼했으며, 이슬람교, 힌두교, 기독교 및 기타 종교의 요소를 결합한 철학적 융합체인 딘이일라히를 그의 궁정에서 만들었습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">아크바르와 그 후계자들 하의 무굴 시대는 페르시아, 인도, 중앙아시아 이슬람 요소를 독특한 인도-이슬람 건축 양식으로 결합한 놀라운 예술적·건축적 발전을 목격했으며, 이 전통은 훗날 아크바르의 손자 샤 자한이 건설한 타지마할 같은 걸작을 탄생시켰습니다.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Akbar",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 아크바르",
          source2: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.worldhistory.org/Akbar/",
          sourceSnippet2: "World History Encyclopedia — 아크바르"
        },
        zh: {
          title: "莫卧儿帝国与阿克巴大帝：文化融合的巅峰",
          desc: "阿克巴大帝以革命性的宗教宽容政策统治莫卧儿帝国，统一了印度次大陆大部分地区，同时创造了独特的印度教-伊斯兰文化融合。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">莫卧儿帝国建立于1526年，由来自中亚、帖木儿和成吉思汗后裔巴布尔建立，他在第一次帕尼帕特战役中成功击败德里苏丹国，为印度历史上最具影响力的帝国之一奠定了基础。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">该帝国在巴布尔之孙阿克巴统治下达到鼎盛，阿克巴年仅13岁便于1556年登基，后来发展成为印度历史上最具远见的统治者之一，通过军事征服与同印度教拉杰普特统治者的外交联盟相结合扩大帝国领土。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">阿克巴尤以远超其时代的宗教宽容政策著称，废除了给非穆斯林公民带来负担的人头税，迎娶印度教拉杰普特公主，并在宫廷中创立了融合伊斯兰教、印度教、基督教及其他宗教元素的哲学融合体\"神圣宗教\"（din-i-ilahi）。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">阿克巴及其继任者统治下的莫卧儿时代见证了非凡的艺术与建筑发展，将波斯、印度和中亚伊斯兰元素融合成独特的印度-伊斯兰建筑风格，这一传统后来诞生了阿克巴之孙沙贾汗建造的泰姬陵等杰作。</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Akbar",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 阿克巴",
          source2: "World History Encyclopedia",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.worldhistory.org/Akbar/",
          sourceSnippet2: "World History Encyclopedia — 阿克巴"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      id: "india-british-raj-kolonialisme",
      langs: {
        id: {
          title: "British Raj: Satu Abad Kekuasaan Kolonial Inggris di India",
          desc: "Mahkota Inggris mengambil alih kekuasaan langsung atas India pada 1858 setelah Pemberontakan Besar 1857, mengawali era British Raj yang mengeksploitasi ekonomi India sekaligus membangun infrastruktur kolonial ekstensif.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Kekuasaan Inggris di India awalnya berkembang melalui East India Company, perusahaan dagang yang secara bertahap memperluas kendali politik dan militernya atas berbagai wilayah India sepanjang abad ke-18 dan awal abad ke-19, memanfaatkan kemunduran Kekaisaran Mughal dan perpecahan di antara para penguasa lokal.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Pemberontakan Besar 1857, yang dipicu ketegangan agama, ekonomi, dan militer termasuk kontroversi peluru senapan yang dilapisi lemak babi dan sapi, melibatkan pemberontakan luas pasukan sepoy India terhadap East India Company, sebuah perlawanan yang meski akhirnya dipadamkan secara brutal, mengguncang fondasi kekuasaan kolonial Inggris.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Pascapemberontakan tersebut, Mahkota Inggris secara resmi mengambil alih kekuasaan langsung atas India pada 1858 melalui Government of India Act, mengakhiri kekuasaan East India Company dan mendirikan sistem pemerintahan kolonial langsung yang dikenal sebagai British Raj, dengan Ratu Victoria kemudian dinobatkan sebagai Permaisuri India pada 1876.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Era British Raj membawa perubahan ekonomi signifikan termasuk pembangunan jaringan kereta api ekstensif, sistem telegraf, dan infrastruktur irigasi, namun kebijakan ekonomi kolonial secara sistematis mengeksploitasi sumber daya India untuk kepentingan industri Inggris, menghancurkan industri tekstil tradisional India dan menyebabkan berbagai bencana kelaparan besar yang menewaskan jutaan warga India.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Kebijakan diskriminatif rasial dan eksploitasi ekonomi British Raj memicu kebangkitan gerakan nasionalisme India sepanjang akhir abad ke-19 dan awal abad ke-20, dengan pembentukan Kongres Nasional India pada 1885 meletakkan fondasi organisasi bagi perjuangan panjang menuju kemerdekaan yang kelak dipimpin tokoh-tokoh seperti Mahatma Gandhi.</p>",
          source: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/british-in-india/",
          sourceSnippet: "National Archives UK — British in India",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/India/The-British-Raj",
          sourceSnippet2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — The British Raj",
          source3: "BBC News",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-35081178",
          sourceSnippet3: "BBC News — British Raj and colonial rule in India"
        },
        en: {
          title: "The British Raj: A Century of British Colonial Rule in India",
          desc: "The British Crown took direct control of India in 1858 following the Great Rebellion of 1857, beginning the British Raj era that exploited India's economy while building extensive colonial infrastructure.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">British power in India initially developed through the East India Company, a trading corporation that gradually expanded its political and military control over various Indian territories throughout the 18th and early 19th centuries, exploiting the decline of the Mughal Empire and divisions among local rulers.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The Great Rebellion of 1857, triggered by religious, economic, and military tensions including the controversy over rifle cartridges greased with pig and cow fat, involved widespread rebellion by Indian sepoy troops against the East India Company, a resistance that, though eventually brutally suppressed, shook the foundations of British colonial power.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Following this rebellion, the British Crown officially took direct control of India in 1858 through the Government of India Act, ending East India Company rule and establishing the direct colonial governance system known as the British Raj, with Queen Victoria subsequently crowned Empress of India in 1876.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The British Raj era brought significant economic changes including the construction of extensive railway networks, telegraph systems, and irrigation infrastructure, but colonial economic policies systematically exploited Indian resources for British industrial benefit, destroying India's traditional textile industry and causing various major famines that killed millions of Indian citizens.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The British Raj's racially discriminatory policies and economic exploitation sparked the rise of Indian nationalist movements throughout the late 19th and early 20th centuries, with the formation of the Indian National Congress in 1885 laying the organizational foundation for the long struggle toward independence later led by figures such as Mahatma Gandhi.</p>",
          source: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/british-in-india/",
          sourceSnippet: "National Archives UK — British in India",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/India/The-British-Raj",
          sourceSnippet2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — The British Raj",
          source3: "BBC News",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-35081178",
          sourceSnippet3: "BBC News — British Raj and colonial rule in India"
        },
        ja: {
          title: "英領インド帝国：インドにおける1世紀のイギリス植民地支配",
          desc: "イギリス王室は1857年の大反乱後の1858年にインドの直接統治権を掌握し、インド経済を搾取すると同時に広範な植民地インフラを構築した英領インド帝国時代を開始した。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">インドにおけるイギリスの権力は当初、東インド会社を通じて発展しました。この貿易会社は18世紀から19世紀初頭にかけて、ムガル帝国の衰退と地方統治者間の分裂を利用しながら、インドの様々な地域に対する政治的・軍事的支配を段階的に拡大しました。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">豚と牛の脂で塗られた銃器薬莢をめぐる論争を含む宗教的・経済的・軍事的緊張によって引き起こされた1857年の大反乱は、東インド会社に対するインド人セポイ部隊による広範な反乱を伴い、最終的には残忍に鎮圧されたものの、イギリス植民地権力の基盤を揺るがしました。</p>",
          source: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/british-in-india/",
          sourceSnippet: "英国国立公文書館 — インドにおけるイギリス",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/India/The-British-Raj",
          sourceSnippet2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 英領インド帝国"
        },
        ko: {
          title: "영국령 인도 제국: 인도에서의 1세기 영국 식민 통치",
          desc: "영국 왕실은 1857년 대반란 이후 1858년 인도에 대한 직접 통치권을 장악하여, 인도 경제를 착취하는 동시에 광범위한 식민지 인프라를 구축한 영국령 인도 제국 시대를 시작했다.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">인도에서 영국의 권력은 처음에는 동인도회사를 통해 발전했는데, 이 무역 회사는 18세기부터 19세기 초까지 무굴 제국의 쇠퇴와 지방 통치자들 간의 분열을 이용하며 인도 각지에 대한 정치적·군사적 지배를 점진적으로 확대했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">돼지와 소 기름으로 코팅된 소총 탄약통을 둘러싼 논란을 포함한 종교적·경제적·군사적 긴장으로 촉발된 1857년 대반란은 동인도회사에 대한 인도 세포이 군대의 광범위한 반란을 수반했으며, 이 저항은 결국 잔혹하게 진압되었지만 영국 식민 권력의 기초를 뒤흔들었습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">이 반란 이후 영국 왕실은 1858년 인도통치법을 통해 공식적으로 인도에 대한 직접 통치권을 장악하여 동인도회사의 통치를 종식시키고 영국령 인도 제국으로 알려진 직접 식민 통치 체제를 수립했으며, 빅토리아 여왕은 이후 1876년 인도 여제로 즉위했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">영국령 인도 제국 시대는 광범위한 철도망, 전신 시스템, 관개 인프라 건설을 포함한 중요한 경제적 변화를 가져왔지만, 식민지 경제 정책은 영국 산업의 이익을 위해 인도 자원을 체계적으로 착취하여 인도의 전통 섬유 산업을 파괴하고 수백만 명의 인도 시민을 사망케 한 various 대기근을 초래했습니다.</p>",
          source: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/british-in-india/",
          sourceSnippet: "영국 국립기록보관소 — 인도의 영국",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/India/The-British-Raj",
          sourceSnippet2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 영국령 인도 제국"
        },
        zh: {
          title: "英属印度：印度百年英国殖民统治",
          desc: "英国王室在1857年印度大起义后于1858年直接掌控印度，开启了英属印度时代，该时代剥削印度经济的同时也建立了广泛的殖民地基础设施。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">英国在印度的权力最初通过东印度公司发展起来，这家贸易公司在18世纪至19世纪初逐渐扩大对印度various地区的政治和军事控制，利用了莫卧儿帝国的衰落以及当地统治者之间的分裂。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">1857年印度大起义由宗教、经济和军事紧张局势引发，包括涂有猪油和牛油的步枪弹药筒引发的争议，涉及印度土兵部队对东印度公司的广泛反抗，这场抵抗虽然最终被残酷镇压，却动摇了英国殖民权力的根基。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">这场起义之后，英国王室于1858年通过《印度政府法案》正式直接掌控印度，结束了东印度公司的统治，建立了被称为英属印度的直接殖民治理体系，维多利亚女王随后于1876年加冕为印度女皇。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">英属印度时代带来了重大经济变化，包括广泛铁路网、电报系统和灌溉基础设施的建设，但殖民经济政策系统性地剥削印度资源以谋取英国工业利益，摧毁了印度传统纺织业，并造成了造成数百万印度公民死亡的various重大饥荒。</p>",
          source: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/british-in-india/",
          sourceSnippet: "英国国家档案馆 — 英国在印度",
          source2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.britannica.com/place/India/The-British-Raj",
          sourceSnippet2: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 英属印度"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      id: "india-gandhi-gerakan-kemerdekaan",
      langs: {
        id: {
          title: "Mahatma Gandhi dan Gerakan Kemerdekaan India: Perlawanan Tanpa Kekerasan",
          desc: "Mahatma Gandhi memimpin gerakan kemerdekaan India melalui filosofi satyagraha (perlawanan tanpa kekerasan), mengorganisir kampanye massal seperti Gerakan Garam dan Quit India yang akhirnya membawa India meraih kemerdekaan.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi kembali ke India pada 1915 setelah dua dekade bekerja sebagai pengacara di Afrika Selatan, di mana ia mengembangkan filosofi satyagraha (kekuatan kebenaran), sebuah metode perlawanan sipil tanpa kekerasan yang kelak menjadi landasan strategi perjuangan kemerdekaan India.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Gandhi memimpin serangkaian kampanye perlawanan sipil skala besar sepanjang 1920-an dan 1930-an, dengan Gerakan Non-Kooperasi 1920-1922 mengajak rakyat India memboikot institusi, sekolah, dan barang-barang Inggris, sementara Gerakan Garam pada 1930, yang melibatkan pawai sejauh 390 kilometer menuju laut untuk memproduksi garam secara ilegal sebagai simbol perlawanan terhadap monopoli garam Inggris, menarik perhatian dunia internasional.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Perang Dunia II membawa ketegangan baru antara Kongres Nasional India dan pemerintah kolonial Inggris, dengan Gandhi meluncurkan Gerakan Quit India pada Agustus 1942, menuntut penarikan penuh Inggris dari India, yang direspons pemerintah kolonial dengan penangkapan massal terhadap Gandhi dan hampir seluruh kepemimpinan Kongres.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Perjuangan kemerdekaan India turut melibatkan tokoh-tokoh penting lainnya termasuk Jawaharlal Nehru yang kelak menjadi perdana menteri pertama India, serta Muhammad Ali Jinnah yang memimpin Liga Muslim dan menuntut pembentukan negara terpisah bagi umat Muslim India, perpecahan yang kelak berujung pada pembagian India dan Pakistan.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Kombinasi tekanan ekonomi pascaperang, meningkatnya gerakan nasionalisme, serta ketidakmampuan Inggris mempertahankan kontrol kolonial akhirnya memaksa pemerintah Inggris menyetujui kemerdekaan India, dengan Gandhi tetap menjadi simbol paling ikonik perjuangan tanpa kekerasan yang menginspirasi gerakan hak-hak sipil di seluruh dunia hingga saat ini.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Mahatma-Gandhi",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — Mahatma Gandhi",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/indian-independence/",
          sourceSnippet2: "National Archives UK — Indian independence movement",
          source3: "BBC News",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-35081178",
          sourceSnippet3: "BBC News — Gandhi and India's independence movement"
        },
        en: {
          title: "Mahatma Gandhi and the Indian Independence Movement: Non-Violent Resistance",
          desc: "Mahatma Gandhi led India's independence movement through the philosophy of satyagraha (non-violent resistance), organizing mass campaigns such as the Salt March and Quit India Movement that ultimately brought India independence.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi returned to India in 1915 after two decades working as a lawyer in South Africa, where he developed the philosophy of satyagraha (truth-force), a method of non-violent civil resistance that would later become the foundation of India's independence struggle strategy.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Gandhi led a series of large-scale civil resistance campaigns throughout the 1920s and 1930s, with the Non-Cooperation Movement of 1920-1922 calling on Indians to boycott British institutions, schools, and goods, while the Salt March in 1930, involving a 390-kilometer march to the sea to illegally produce salt as a symbol of resistance against the British salt monopoly, drew international attention.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">World War II brought new tensions between the Indian National Congress and the British colonial government, with Gandhi launching the Quit India Movement in August 1942, demanding Britain's complete withdrawal from India, which the colonial government responded to with mass arrests of Gandhi and nearly the entire Congress leadership.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">India's independence struggle also involved other important figures including Jawaharlal Nehru, who would later become India's first prime minister, and Muhammad Ali Jinnah, who led the Muslim League and demanded the formation of a separate state for Indian Muslims, a division that would later lead to the partition of India and Pakistan.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">A combination of postwar economic pressure, rising nationalist movements, and Britain's inability to maintain colonial control finally forced the British government to agree to Indian independence, with Gandhi remaining the most iconic symbol of non-violent struggle that continues to inspire civil rights movements worldwide to this day.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Mahatma-Gandhi",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — Mahatma Gandhi",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/indian-independence/",
          sourceSnippet2: "National Archives UK — Indian independence movement",
          source3: "BBC News",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-35081178",
          sourceSnippet3: "BBC News — Gandhi and India's independence movement"
        },
        ja: {
          title: "マハトマ・ガンディーとインド独立運動：非暴力抵抗",
          desc: "マハトマ・ガンディーはサティヤーグラハ（非暴力抵抗）の哲学を通じてインド独立運動を指導し、塩の行進やインドを立ち去れ運動などの大衆キャンペーンを組織し、最終的にインドに独立をもたらした。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">モーハンダース・カラムチャンド・ガンディーは、南アフリカで弁護士として20年間働いた後、1915年にインドに帰国しました。そこで彼はサティヤーグラハ（真理の力）の哲学を発展させ、これが後にインド独立闘争の戦略的基盤となる非暴力市民抵抗の方法となりました。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">ガンディーは1920年代から1930年代にかけて一連の大規模な市民抵抗キャンペーンを指導し、1920〜1922年の非協力運動ではインド人にイギリスの機関、学校、商品のボイコットを呼びかけ、1930年の塩の行進では、イギリスの塩の独占に対する抵抗の象徴として違法に塩を生産するため海まで390キロメートルを行進し、国際的な注目を集めました。</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Mahatma-Gandhi",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — マハトマ・ガンディー",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/indian-independence/",
          sourceSnippet2: "英国国立公文書館 — インド独立運動"
        },
        ko: {
          title: "마하트마 간디와 인도 독립운동: 비폭력 저항",
          desc: "마하트마 간디는 사티아그라하(비폭력 저항) 철학을 통해 인도 독립운동을 이끌었으며, 소금 행진과 인도철수운동 같은 대중 캠페인을 조직해 결국 인도의 독립을 가져왔다.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">모한다스 카람찬드 간디는 남아프리카에서 변호사로 20년간 일한 후 1915년 인도로 돌아왔으며, 그곳에서 사티아그라하(진리의 힘)라는 철학을 발전시켰는데, 이는 훗날 인도 독립 투쟁 전략의 기초가 될 비폭력 시민 저항 방법이었습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">간디는 1920년대와 1930년대에 걸쳐 일련의 대규모 시민 저항 운동을 이끌었으며, 1920-1922년 비협조 운동은 인도인들에게 영국 기관, 학교, 상품에 대한 보이콧을 요청했고, 1930년 소금 행진은 영국의 소금 독점에 대한 저항의 상징으로 불법적으로 소금을 생산하기 위해 바다까지 390킬로미터를 행진하며 국제적 관심을 끌었습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">제2차 세계대전은 인도국민회의와 영국 식민 정부 사이에 새로운 긴장을 가져왔으며, 간디는 1942년 8월 인도철수운동을 개시하여 영국의 인도 완전 철수를 요구했고, 식민 정부는 간디와 거의 전체 회의 지도부를 대량 체포하는 것으로 대응했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">인도 독립 투쟁에는 훗날 인도 초대 총리가 될 자와할랄 네루와, 무슬림 연맹을 이끌며 인도 무슬림을 위한 별도 국가 수립을 요구한 무함마드 알리 진나를 포함한 다른 중요한 인물들도 참여했으며, 이 분열은 훗날 인도와 파키스탄의 분할로 이어졌습니다.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Mahatma-Gandhi",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 마하트마 간디",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/indian-independence/",
          sourceSnippet2: "영국 국립기록보관소 — 인도 독립운동"
        },
        zh: {
          title: "圣雄甘地与印度独立运动：非暴力抵抗",
          desc: "圣雄甘地通过非暴力不合作（真理坚持）哲学领导印度独立运动，组织了食盐进军和退出印度运动等大规模行动，最终为印度带来独立。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">莫罕达斯·卡拉姆昌德·甘地在南非担任律师工作二十年后于1915年返回印度，在那里他发展出非暴力不合作（坚持真理）哲学，这一非暴力公民抵抗方法后来成为印度独立斗争战略的基础。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">甘地在整个1920年代和1930年代领导了一系列大规模公民抵抗运动，1920-1922年的不合作运动呼吁印度人抵制英国机构、学校和商品，而1930年的食盐进军涉及步行390公里前往海边非法制盐，作为反抗英国食盐垄断的象征，吸引了国际关注。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">第二次世界大战给印度国民大会党与英国殖民政府之间带来了新的紧张关系，甘地于1942年8月发起退出印度运动，要求英国完全撤离印度，殖民政府则以大规模逮捕甘地及几乎整个国大党领导层作为回应。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">印度独立斗争还涉及其他重要人物，包括后来成为印度首任总理的贾瓦哈拉尔·尼赫鲁，以及领导穆斯林联盟并要求为印度穆斯林建立独立国家的穆罕默德·阿里·真纳，这一分裂后来导致了印度和巴基斯坦的分治。</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/biography/Mahatma-Gandhi",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 圣雄甘地",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/indian-independence/",
          sourceSnippet2: "英国国家档案馆 — 印度独立运动"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      id: "india-partisi-kemerdekaan-1947",
      langs: {
        id: {
          title: "Partisi India (1947): Kemerdekaan yang Diwarnai Tragedi Kemanusiaan Terbesar",
          desc: "India meraih kemerdekaan pada 15 Agustus 1947, namun bersamaan dengan pembagian wilayah menjadi India dan Pakistan yang memicu salah satu perpindahan penduduk massal dan kekerasan komunal terbesar dalam sejarah modern.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">Pemerintah Inggris di bawah Perdana Menteri Clement Attlee mengumumkan komitmen untuk memberikan kemerdekaan India pada Februari 1947, mengirim Lord Louis Mountbatten sebagai Gubernur Jenderal terakhir dengan mandat mempercepat proses transfer kekuasaan yang awalnya direncanakan berlangsung hingga Juni 1948.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Ketegangan komunal yang meningkat tajam antara komunitas Hindu, Muslim, dan Sikh, dikombinasikan dengan tuntutan Liga Muslim yang dipimpin Muhammad Ali Jinnah untuk negara terpisah, memaksa Mountbatten mempercepat jadwal kemerdekaan secara dramatis menjadi Agustus 1947, dengan garis batas partisi yang dirancang pengacara Inggris Cyril Radcliffe hanya dalam waktu beberapa minggu tanpa pengetahuan mendalam tentang geografi dan demografi lokal.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">India dan Pakistan secara resmi meraih kemerdekaan pada 15 Agustus 1947, dengan wilayah dibagi berdasarkan mayoritas agama menjadi India yang mayoritas Hindu dan Pakistan (terdiri dari Pakistan Barat dan Pakistan Timur yang kelak menjadi Bangladesh) yang mayoritas Muslim, pembagian yang memaksa jutaan warga pindah melintasi batas negara baru berdasarkan identitas agama mereka.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Partisi tersebut memicu salah satu perpindahan penduduk massal terbesar dalam sejarah manusia, dengan diperkirakan 10-20 juta orang mengungsi melintasi perbatasan baru India-Pakistan, disertai kekerasan komunal brutal yang menewaskan antara 200.000 hingga dua juta orang dalam pembantaian, kekerasan seksual, dan bentrokan antaragama yang meluas.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Trauma Partisi 1947 terus membayangi hubungan India-Pakistan hingga saat ini, memicu berbagai konflik dan perang antara kedua negara sepanjang dekade-dekade berikutnya, sementara warisan kemerdekaan yang dipimpin Gandhi dan para pemimpin nasionalis lainnya tetap menjadi momen paling penting dalam sejarah modern anak benua India meski diwarnai tragedi kemanusiaan besar tersebut.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/event/Partition-of-India",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — Partition of India",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/partition-of-india/",
          sourceSnippet2: "National Archives UK — Partition of India records",
          source3: "BBC News",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-40670308",
          sourceSnippet3: "BBC News — India's partition remembered 70 years on"
        },
        en: {
          title: "The Partition of India (1947): Independence Marked by the Greatest Humanitarian Tragedy",
          desc: "India gained independence on August 15, 1947, but simultaneously with the division of territory into India and Pakistan, triggering one of the largest mass population displacements and communal violence events in modern history.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">The British government under Prime Minister Clement Attlee announced its commitment to grant Indian independence in February 1947, sending Lord Louis Mountbatten as the last Governor-General with a mandate to accelerate the power transfer process originally planned to last until June 1948.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">Sharply escalating communal tensions between Hindu, Muslim, and Sikh communities, combined with demands from the Muslim League led by Muhammad Ali Jinnah for a separate state, forced Mountbatten to dramatically accelerate the independence timeline to August 1947, with the partition boundary line designed by British lawyer Cyril Radcliffe in just a few weeks without deep knowledge of local geography and demographics.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">India and Pakistan officially gained independence on August 15, 1947, with territory divided based on religious majority into predominantly Hindu India and predominantly Muslim Pakistan (comprising West Pakistan and East Pakistan, which later became Bangladesh), a division that forced millions of citizens to relocate across new national borders based on their religious identity.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">This partition triggered one of the largest mass population displacements in human history, with an estimated 10-20 million people displaced across the new India-Pakistan border, accompanied by brutal communal violence that killed between 200,000 to two million people in widespread massacres, sexual violence, and interreligious clashes.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">The trauma of the 1947 Partition continues to overshadow India-Pakistan relations to this day, triggering various conflicts and wars between the two nations throughout subsequent decades, while the legacy of independence led by Gandhi and other nationalist leaders remains the most important moment in the modern history of the Indian subcontinent despite being marked by this great humanitarian tragedy.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/event/Partition-of-India",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — Partition of India",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/partition-of-india/",
          sourceSnippet2: "National Archives UK — Partition of India records",
          source3: "BBC News",
          sourceUrl3: "https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-40670308",
          sourceSnippet3: "BBC News — India's partition remembered 70 years on"
        },
        ja: {
          title: "インド分割（1947年）：最大の人道的悲劇に彩られた独立",
          desc: "インドは1947年8月15日に独立を達成したが、同時にインドとパキスタンへの領土分割が行われ、近代史上最大級の大規模人口移動と共同体間暴力の一つを引き起こした。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">クレメント・アトリー首相率いるイギリス政府は1947年2月、インド独立を認める約束を発表し、当初1948年6月まで続く予定だった権力移譲プロセスを加速する任務を負った最後の総督としてルイス・マウントバッテン卿を派遣しました。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">ヒンドゥー教、イスラム教、シク教コミュニティ間の急激に高まる共同体間の緊張は、ムハンマド・アリー・ジンナー率いるムスリム連盟による独立国家の要求と相まって、マウントバッテンに独立の日程を1947年8月へと劇的に前倒しすることを強いました。分割の境界線はイギリスの弁護士シリル・ラドクリフによって、現地の地理と人口動態に関する深い知識なしにわずか数週間で設計されました。</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/event/Partition-of-India",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — インド分割",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/partition-of-india/",
          sourceSnippet2: "英国国立公文書館 — インド分割の記録"
        },
        ko: {
          title: "인도 분할 (1947년): 최대의 인도주의적 비극으로 얼룩진 독립",
          desc: "인도는 1947년 8월 15일 독립을 이루었지만, 동시에 인도와 파키스탄으로의 영토 분할이 이루어져 현대사에서 가장 큰 대규모 인구 이동과 공동체 폭력 사건 중 하나를 촉발했다.",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">클레멘트 애틀리 총리 하의 영국 정부는 1947년 2월 인도 독립 부여에 대한 약속을 발표하며, 당초 1948년 6월까지 지속될 예정이었던 권력 이양 과정을 가속화하는 임무를 맡은 마지막 총독으로 루이스 마운트배튼 경을 파견했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">힌두교, 이슬람교, 시크교 공동체 간의 급격히 고조되는 긴장은 무함마드 알리 진나가 이끄는 무슬림 연맹의 별도 국가 요구와 결합되어, 마운트배튼이 독립 일정을 1947년 8월로 극적으로 앞당기도록 강요했으며, 분할 경계선은 영국 변호사 시릴 래드클리프가 현지 지리와 인구 통계에 대한 깊은 지식 없이 불과 몇 주 만에 설계했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">인도와 파키스탄은 1947년 8월 15일 공식적으로 독립을 얻었으며, 영토는 종교적 다수에 따라 힌두교가 다수인 인도와 이슬람교가 다수인 파키스탄(서파키스탄과 훗날 방글라데시가 된 동파키스탄으로 구성)으로 나뉘었으며, 이 분할은 수백만 시민이 종교적 정체성에 따라 새로운 국경을 넘어 이주하도록 강요했습니다.</p><p class=\"mb-4\">이 분할은 인류 역사상 가장 큰 대규모 인구 이동 중 하나를 촉발했으며, 추정 1000만~2000만 명이 새로운 인도-파키스탄 국경을 넘어 이주했고, 광범위한 대학살, 성폭력, 종교 간 충돌로 20만~200만 명이 사망하는 잔혹한 공동체 폭력을 동반했습니다.</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/event/Partition-of-India",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 인도 분할",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/partition-of-india/",
          sourceSnippet2: "영국 국립기록보관소 — 인도 분할 기록"
        },
        zh: {
          title: "印度分治（1947年）：伴随最大人道主义悲剧的独立",
          desc: "印度于1947年8月15日获得独立，但同时印巴分治也引发了现代史上最大规模的人口迁移和社群暴力事件之一。",
          content: "<p class=\"mb-4\">克莱门特·艾德礼首相领导的英国政府于1947年2月宣布承诺给予印度独立，派遣路易斯·蒙巴顿勋爵作为最后一任总督，其使命是加快原计划持续到1948年6月的权力移交进程。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">印度教、穆斯林和锡克教社区之间急剧升级的社群紧张关系，加上穆罕默德·阿里·真纳领导的穆斯林联盟要求建立独立国家，迫使蒙巴顿将独立时间表急剧提前至1947年8月，分治边界线由英国律师西里尔·拉德克利夫在短短几周内设计完成，且对当地地理和人口状况缺乏深入了解。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">印度和巴基斯坦于1947年8月15日正式获得独立，领土按宗教多数划分为以印度教徒为主的印度和以穆斯林为主的巴基斯坦（由西巴基斯坦和后来成为孟加拉国的东巴基斯坦组成），这一分治迫使数百万公民根据其宗教身份迁移至新的国界线两侧。</p><p class=\"mb-4\">这次分治引发了人类历史上最大规模的人口迁移之一，估计有1000万至2000万人在新的印巴边境两侧流离失所，伴随着造成20万至200万人死亡的残酷社群暴力，包括广泛的大屠杀、性暴力和宗教间冲突。</p>",
          source: "Encyclopaedia Britannica",
          sourceUrl: "https://www.britannica.com/event/Partition-of-India",
          sourceSnippet: "Encyclopaedia Britannica — 印度分治",
          source2: "National Archives UK",
          sourceUrl2: "https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/help-with-your-research/research-guides/partition-of-india/",
          sourceSnippet2: "英国国家档案馆 — 印度分治记录"
        }
      }
    }
